    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-28T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-28T09:00:00-05:00" n="321"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d321">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/2805: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Denmark</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-28T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 28, 1918—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10.48 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3222. Your 1221, November 18, 7 p.m.<note n="13" xml:id="d321fn13">Not printed;
                        it transmitted the queries listed in telegram No. 112, Nov. 16. 1918, 3
                        p.m., from Colonel House, <ref target="frus1919Parisv01#pg_197">vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 197</ref>.</note> Query 4. Danish press
                    on November 13 reported on the aversion [<hi rend="italic">assurance?</hi>] of a
                    Vienna newspaper, that Roumania had sent Hungary an ultimatum demanding that
                    Siebenbuergen be immediately evacuated and left to the Roumanian Crown. Further
                    details not given. Danish press reports this morning that Roumanian forces have
                    actually occupied extensive Hungarian territories, and that fears are expressed
                    in Budapest that the occupation will include all districts up to the capital.
                    Repeated to House, referring his 112, November 16, 3 p.m. to Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grant-Smith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
